{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e214f619-77e4-42e7-8a48-c730d9f4f062","content":"No repo-specific guidance here, but this is a well-known migration. Here's what you need to do:\n\n### Remove the VSTest opt-in\n\nIn your project file, **delete** (or set to `false`) the property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove this line -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's it. With **MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0**, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner. The `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property was explicitly opting you back into the legacy runner. Removing it switches you to Microsoft.Testing.Platform automatically.\n\n### Key differences to be aware of\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **Run tests** | `dotnet test` still works, but you can also run the test project directly: `dotnet run --project MyTests.csproj` |\n| **CLI flags** | Some VSTest switches (e.g. `--filter`) change syntax. Use `dotnet test --help` to see the new options. |\n| **`.runsettings`** | Still supported, but some adapter-specific settings may need updating. |\n| **CI/CD** | If your pipeline uses `dotnet test --logger trx`, it still works. Verify TRX output paths. |\n\n### Quick validation\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --no-build   # confirm tests still discover & pass\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c3ea36fb-3cf5-430d-8c89-174caa238e43","outputTokens":331,"requestId":"2873:2F77E2:16AC07A:180DC09:6A045FD5"},"id":"dfb66559-7cdd-41f5-9899-40fb9efd7a8f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:23.431Z","parentId":"a77364a9-306a-493e-af08-763b9b0c8bed"}
